history.content:
I took CS 186 with Hellerstein + Gonzalez in Spring 2016. They're both great lecturers - it was pretty easy to pick up the material from webcasts. They provided many examples in their lecture slides to supplement different concepts. IIRC Hellerstein webcasted himself doing a practice final, explaining his thought process to help students understand the material (he really cares!). I heard the class has changed quite a bit since then, so I can't comment on the class organization.

As for who to take the class with, I would choose Hellerstein since he is more experienced. However, they're both great professors.
